Description of the Field: ArcGIS Object ID

County FIPS Codes are unique 5-digit codes that represent specific US counties. The first two digits represent the county's state and the last three digits represent the county. For example "49017" is the FIPS Code for Garfield County, Utah. "49" represents Utah and "017" represents Garfield County.

Age: Population Age 65 and Older

Because the indicator datasets are so large, FEMA binned the datasets and assigned consistent color ramps for the bins to provide a visual cue for users to quickly identify ranges for the data. These bins and associated colors provide a more immediate high-level understanding of a geographic area’s characteristics.
